.container.main-container#interactive-content
  #stage-0.stage.row.justify-content-center
    .col-12.col-md-10
      h2.text-center Height
    .col-12.col-md-10.d-flex-justify-content-center.text-center.mt-4
      = image_tag image_url('gender-differences/start-graph.png'), class: "img img-fluid start-graph", alt: ""
    .col-12.col-md-10.d-flex.justify-content-center
      p.mt-4
        span.d-legened.d-legened-4 aria-live='height'
          em d 
          |= 2.60
    .col-12.col-md-10
      p.text-left 
       |Here are two curves that represent the distribution of height for 100 men (in blue) and 100 women (in red). The center line in each curve represents the mean, or average height, for each gender. The difference between the two means is large and can be quantified as 
       em d 
       |= 2.6. In this example, 
       em d 
       |is a measure of effect size, or a way to quantify how different two means are from each other. The larger the number the bigger the effect or difference between the two groups. These data support your intuition that men are, on average, taller than women. But notice that despite the difference in the averages, some women are still taller than some men (the distributions are overlapping).
    .col-12.col-md-10.d-flex.justify-content-center
      p.text-left.mb-0 Next, let's take a look at several personality traits. You will be asked to move the distributions to guess the difference between the average scores for men and women. Select "Next" to continue.
  #stage-1.stage.row.justify-content-center.d-none
    .maintext.maintext-1.col-12.col-md-10.text-left
      h2.text-center Aggression
    .image-container.col-12.col-md-10
      = image_tag image_url('gender-differences/aggression-graph.png'), class: "img img-fluid graph-line graph containment-wrapper", alt: ""
      = image_tag image_url('gender-differences/men-data.png'), class: "img img-fluid data men-data men-data-1", alt: ""
      = image_tag image_url('gender-differences/woman-data.png'), class: "img img-fluid data woman-data woman-data-1", alt: ""
    .data-container.col-12.col-md-10.justify-content-center.mt-4.mb-2
      .sliders.mx-auto
        .slider-range-max.slider-1
    .col-12.col-md-10.d-flex.d-flex.justify-content-center
      p.mt-4
        span.d-legened.d-legened-1 aria-live='aggression'
          em d 
          |= 2.60
    .feedback.feedback-1.col-12.col-md-10.mt-4.incomplete
      p.mb-0
        |For this example, slide the two curves to estimate what you believe is the average gender difference in physical aggression. The gender that you believe is more physically aggressive should be farther on the right. The 
        em d 
        |score tells you how large you think this difference will be. When you’re ready, select “Submit.”
